oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Dairy Herd Reproductive Performance Parameters Relevant to North American Production and Marketing Systems
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Etherington, W. G.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: dairy herd reproduction
herd reproductive performance
herd reproductive management
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The objective of this presentation is to describe some reproductive performance parameters which can be used to assess the level of reproductive management in a dairy herd. An attempt will also be made to describe how some reproductive performance diagnostic indices can be used as an indicator of the areas of management which are causing reproductive problems in herds.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: American Association of Bovine Practitioners Conference Proceedings; 1985; 32-36
